The paper presents a method for improving the performance of support vector machines (SVMs) through dropout training with data augmentation. This is a topic related to machine learning and specifically to SVMs, which are commonly used in computer vision (CV) and natural language processing (NLP) applications. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the use of latent representations, which are commonly used in neural networks, suggesting a possible connection to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses the use of logistic regression, which is a common technique in natural language processing (NLP), suggesting a possible connection to cs.CL (Computation and Language).
